{"parentUuid":"3e1ed142-4970-4ee6-a7b4-ec999a482ddf","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"mcp_instructions_delta","addedNames":["honeycomb"],"addedBlocks":["## honeycomb\nHoneycomb MCP Server - Observability Data Query Interface\n\nIMPORTANT: Follow this workflow for best results:\n\n1. START by getting context:\n   - Use 'get_workspace_context' to understand which team you're working with, available environments, and default environment datasets\n   - Use 'list_environments' to see available environments\n   - Use 'list_datasets' to explore datasets in the chosen environment\n\n2. BEFORE running queries:\n   - Use 'get_dataset_columns' to see all columns for a specific dataset\n   - Use 'find_columns' to discover relevant columns based on your query intent\n   - ALWAYS validate column names exist before using them in queries\n\n3. Query workflow:\n   - Start with 'run_query' using validated column names\n   - Use 'get_query_history' to review previous queries for the team\n   - Use 'get_trace' to drill into specific trace IDs from query results\n\n4. Additional context:\n   - Use 'get_triggers' and 'get_slos' to understand alerts and SLOs\n   - Use 'feedback' to report issues or suggestions\n\nRemember: Column validation is critical - queries will fail if columns don't exist in the dataset."],"removedNames":[]},"type":"attachment","uuid":"dd56f0ab-8a3f-4958-a4a0-7c23f40eb727","timestamp":"2026-05-19T09:34:32.704Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"c6533991-5707-4094-a756-614132c9eb65","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main"}
