{"parentUuid":"c1f19231-fb2b-4b16-93ce-0ff6f52bcdf0","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01SNgycX9USY4pJDPECL7rNd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Diagnosis confirmed exactly. The key lines:\n\n```\n[httptrace] POST git-receive-pack GotConn reused=true wasIdle=true idle=13.001639584s local=192.168.1.114:50582 remote=104.18.16.116:443\n[httptrace] POST git-receive-pack WroteRequest err=use of closed network connection\n```\n\n- **Same socket** (`192.168.1.114:50582` ↔ `104.18.16.116:443`) reused from the info/refs GET\n- **Idle for ~13s** — Cloudflare's edge closed it during that window\n- **`WroteRequest` returned the error** → no bytes reached the server, so this is a transparent connection-pool race, not a server-side rejection of any data\n\nThe previous \"buffer to temp file for Content-Length\" proposal would not have helped — the failure happens before any body byte goes out.\n\n**Fix options**\n\nThree real candidates, in order from cheapest to most robust:\n\n**Fix A — short `IdleConnTimeout` on the HTTP transport.** One-line change in `NewHTTPTransport`. Set e.g. `tc.IdleConnTimeout = 5 * time.Second` so pooled connections expire client-side before any reasonable CDN closes them server-side. Trades a small loss of pool reuse for race-freedom in the long-gap case.\n- ✅ trivial\n- ⚠️ heuristic — if some endpoint closes in 4s we're back to the same bug\n\n**Fix B — explicit `CloseIdleConnections()` before the receive-pack POST.** In `PostRPCStreamBody`, when `service == \"git-receive-pack\"`, drop idle connections first. We know push always follows fetch work, so the connection is guaranteed stale-suspect.\n- ✅ no heuristic, no buffering\n- ⚠️ always costs one extra TLS handshake on the push\n- ⚠️ doesn't help other long-gap call paths (none today, but a foot-gun for the future)\n\n**Fix C — buffer the pack body and set `req.GetBody` so Go's transport auto-retries.** Spool the pack to a temp file, send with explicit `ContentLength`, point `GetBody` at a fresh reader. Go's `http.Transport.shouldRetryRequest` will then retry POST on `pconnBroken` / `nothingWrittenError` (which is what this is) because it knows the body can be replayed.\n- ✅ most robust — handles any idle timeout, anywhere\n- ✅ same code shape as upstream git (which also buffers receive-pack)\n- ⚠️ disk space for the temp file (bounded by `DefaultMaxMaterializedObjects = 500K`, could be GBs)\n- ⚠️ encoder must complete before send starts → slightly worse first-byte latency\n\n**My recommendation**\n\n**Do A + B together:**\n- A as a defense-in-depth default — cheap, helps every code path\n- B as the targeted fix for the known long-gap site\n\nSkip C for now. It's correct but heavier, and the original motivation (Content-Length / chunked encoding) turned out to be a red herring. If A + B doesn't hold up against some other CDN, C is still on the table.\n\nBoth A and B are ~5 lines of code. Want me to implement them?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89854,"cache_read_input_tokens":17247,"output_tokens":6292,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89854,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":6292,"cache_read_input_tokens":17247,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89854},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"previous_message_not_found"}}},"requestId":"req_011CbC4Q9SH5DUbq58yU5sH8","type":"assistant","uuid":"1c7f07bb-e8f6-4a39-9a18-d9f14ff5bc9a","timestamp":"2026-05-19T14:10:10.383Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"c6533991-5707-4094-a756-614132c9eb65","version":